<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1505,2035]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
Comments: According to the original description, the 
<typeStatus box="[816,864,1578,1604]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1006,1148,1577,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[1006,1025,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1041,1148,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in 
<collectionCode box="[1216,1297,1578,1604]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">MNHP</collectionCode>
, however, it was not found there. 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[389,540,1613,1639]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="237 - 350" refId="ref9913" refString="Friese, H. (1901 [1900]) Monographie der Bienengattung Centris (s. lat). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, Wien, 15, 237 - 350." type="journal article" year="1901">Friese (1901)</bibRefCitation>
had already noticed the 
<typeStatus box="[817,865,1614,1640]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
was not available for study when he published his monograph on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[319,401,1650,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,401,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Centris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more than a century ago. The depository and the current condition of the 
<typeStatus box="[1214,1273,1650,1676]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">types</typeStatus>
of this species remain unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1505,2035]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[199,396,1721,1747]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the female of this species has head and mesosoma black with black hairs, except mesoscutum, mesoscutellum (“dorsum”) and the anterior area of the wings insertion (pronotal lobe?) with yellow pubescence; metasoma and legs black with blackish hairs; spine (tibial spur?) of hind legs long, brownish; wings violaceus, not translucent. This description fits relatively well with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[986,1100,1829,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[986,1005,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1019,1100,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[1115,1204,1829,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis box="[1115,1134,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1148,1204,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">lutea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1260,1379,1829,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsata">
<emphasis box="[1260,1279,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1293,1379,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">dorsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The first species was also described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[536,730,1865,1891]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
so probably it is not the same species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1156,1331,1865,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsata">
<emphasis box="[1156,1331,1865,1892]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Centris dorsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the conspicuous, short, yellow pubescence on distal terga, and according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[997,1216,1901,1928]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref10644" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1079,1128,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
it does not occur in 
<collectingRegion box="[151,420,1937,1964]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Rio Grande do Sul state</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[430,575,1937,1964]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis box="[430,575,1937,1964]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Centris lutea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only a few or no yellow hairs on the pronotal lobe, being restricted to the mesoscutum and mesoscutellum. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Silveira, F. A. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B." box="[680,912,1973,2000]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" refId="ref11263" refString="Silveira, F. A., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Almeida, E. A. B. (2002) Abelhas brasileiras Sistematica e Identificacao. Fundacao Araucaria, Belo Horizonte, 254 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Silveira 
<emphasis box="[774,823,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. (2002)
</bibRefCitation>
this species has not been recorded in Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,223,2009,2035]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,152,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">
<bibRefCitation author="Michener, C. D. &amp; Lange, R. B." box="[199,493,152,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="69 - 96" refId="ref10212" refString="Michener, C. D. &amp; Lange, R. B. (1958) Observations on the ethology of Neotropical Anthophorine bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 39, 69 - 96." type="journal article" year="1958">Michener &amp; Lange (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, citing articles published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Silvestri, F." box="[811,985,153,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 216" refId="ref11305" refString="Silvestri, F. (1903) Contribuzione alla connoscenza dei termitidi e termitofili dell'America Meridionale. Redia Giornale di Entomologia, 1, 1 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 137413" type="journal article" year="1903">Silvestri (1903)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pickel, B." box="[1038,1191,153,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="135 - 143" refId="ref10867" refString="Pickel, B. (1928) Contribuicao para a biologia de Centris sponsa e Acanthopus excellens (Hymenoptera). Boletim Biologico, Sao Paulo, 14, 135 - 143." type="journal article" year="1928">Pickel (1928)</bibRefCitation>
, indicated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[1359,1378,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nests in termite mounds, and according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ihering, R." box="[711,874,189,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="461 - 481" refId="ref10131" refString="Ihering, R. (1904) Biologia das abelhas solitarias do Brazil. Revista do Museu Paulista, 6, 461 - 481." type="journal article" year="1904">Ihering (1904)</bibRefCitation>
their nests are attacked by the cleptoparasitic bee 
<taxonomicName authority="(Olivier, 1789)" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1789" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[151,585,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Acanthopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus">
<emphasis box="[151,411,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Acanthopus splendidus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, A. G." box="[426,577,225,251]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="46 - 84" refId="ref10725" refString="Olivier, A. G. (1789) Abeille. In: Diderot, M. M. &amp; D'Alembert (Eds.), Encyclopedie Methodique. Histoire Naturelle. Insectes. Vol. 4. Pankouke, Paris, pp. 46 - 84." type="book chapter" year="1789">Olivier, 1789</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[601,688,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Apidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell &amp; Atkins" authorityYear="1902" box="[698,837,225,252]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ericrocidini">Ericrocidini</taxonomicName>
). This latter species has been recorded only attacking nests of species of the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[522,541,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[565,680,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Ptilotopus</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, J. C. F." box="[697,824,261,287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref10156" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1810) Einige neue Piezantengattungen. Magazin des Gesellschaft naturforschender Freunde, 4, 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="1810">Klug, 1810</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rocha-Filho, L. C. &amp; Morato, E. F. &amp; Melo, G. A. R." box="[840,1122,261,287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="299 - 304" refId="ref11069" refString="Rocha-Filho, L. C., Morato, E. F. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (2009) New host records of Aglaomelissa duckei and a compilation of host associations of Ericrocidini bees (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Zoologia, 26, 299 - 304." type="journal article" year="2009">
Rocha-Filho 
<emphasis box="[990,1040,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
., 2009
</bibRefCitation>
), whose females effectively nest in termite mounds. Considering this information, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[759,898,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[759,778,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[791,898,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might belong to that subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,152,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">
In 1913, Schrottky cited 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[484,625,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[484,503,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[518,625,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[665,770,333,359]" name="Paraguay" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, apparently confusing this name with that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1876" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectoralis">
<emphasis box="[1290,1309,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">pectoralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Burmeister, H." box="[151,349,369,395]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="151 - 183" refId="ref9540" refString="Burmeister, H. (1876) Hymenopterologische Mittheilungen. Stettinger Entomologische Zeitung, 37, 151 - 183." type="journal article" year="1876">Burmeister, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[602,731,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[602,621,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[636,731,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This can be inferred by the existence of a male identified by him as 
<taxonomicName box="[236,445,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[236,445,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Hemisia thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectionCode box="[485,577,405,431]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/6yx0-3nm7" name="Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">MZUSP</collectionCode>
(data labels: 97207 [printed]\ asuncion 
<date box="[1036,1165,405,431]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" value="1910-06-22">1910/22 06</date>
[handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lep)" authorityName="Lep" baseAuthorityName="Lep" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Hemisia thoracica</emphasis>
(Lep)
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[334,355,441,467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
[handwritten] C. Schrottky det. 19 [printed] 12 [handwritten]) that effectively corresponds to the latter species. In 2002a, Moure mentioned he found a female specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[988,1094,477,503]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
identified by Smith as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[1358,1377,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that actually corresponds to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[541,659,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsata">
<emphasis box="[541,560,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[573,659,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">dorsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it is not clear if Smith indeed studied the 
<typeStatus box="[1239,1287,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">type</typeStatus>
of Lepeletier to identify that specimen. The last article citing 
<taxonomicName box="[687,827,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[687,706,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[720,827,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[1035,1255,549,575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref10644" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1117,1166,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
who included it in the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[331,350,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1996" box="[372,506,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Melacentris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[372,506,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Melacentris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (= 
<emphasis box="[554,573,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[595,757,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Melanocentris</emphasis>
), see 
<bibRefCitation author="Vivallo, F." box="[821,978,585,611]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref11640" refString="Vivallo, F. (2018) Taxonomic note on the type species of Centris (Melanocentris). Journal of Melittology, 77, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.17161 / jom. v 0 i 77.7100" type="journal article" year="2018">Vivallo, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Taking into account these facts, the real identity of this species and the subgenus it belongs remain unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,152,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">
Unfortunately, the species of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[528,723,657,683]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
currently housed at 
<collectionCode box="[952,1029,657,683]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/q2xn-ty4w" name="Museo Civico DI Storia Naturale DI Torino" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">MSNT</collectionCode>
were not available to be included in this study. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[429,652,693,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref10644" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[511,562,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
they are 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moure" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[758,892,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolata">
<emphasis box="[758,777,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[792,892,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">lineolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[907,1012,693,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">lectotype</typeStatus>
female designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[1269,1428,693,720]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="97 - 160" refId="ref10320" refString="Moure, J. S. (1960 a) Notes on the types of the Neotropical bees described by Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Studia Entomologica, Rio de Janeiro, 3, 97 - 160." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure, 1960a</bibRefCitation>
) (= 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1804))" authorityName="" authorityYear="1804" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[183,555,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[183,344,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Centris similis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[359,537,729,755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" refId="ref9836" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1804) Systema Piezatorum secundum ordines, genera, species, adjectis synonymis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Reichard, Brunsvigae, 439 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10490" type="book" year="1804">Fabricius, 1804</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[566,726,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emarginata">
<emphasis box="[566,585,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[598,726,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">emarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[740,845,729,755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">lectotype</typeStatus>
female designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Seabra, C. A. C." box="[1093,1349,729,756]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="109 - 117" refId="ref10601" refString="Moure, J. S. &amp; Seabra, C. A. C. (1960) Sobre a identidade de algumas especies de Centris (Hymenoptera - Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 9, 109 - 117." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure &amp; Seabra, 1960</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[1411,1430,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,246,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(valid 
<typeStatus box="[324,427,765,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Seabra, C. A. C." box="[717,972,765,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="109 - 117" refId="ref10601" refString="Moure, J. S. &amp; Seabra, C. A. C. (1960) Sobre a identidade de algumas especies de Centris (Hymenoptera - Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 9, 109 - 117." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure &amp; Seabra, 1960</bibRefCitation>
according to the Article 74.6 of the 
<collectionCode box="[1371,1436,765,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">ICZN</collectionCode>
code). All those specimens were collected in Cayenne, 
<collectingCountry box="[785,953,801,827]" name="French Guiana" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
and they belonged to Serville’s collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[159,346,837,863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier, 1841</bibRefCitation>
). Between those three species only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[740,867,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[740,759,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[772,867,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently considered valid and a redescription of the 
<typeStatus box="[193,296,873,899]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">lectotype</typeStatus>
male can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Seabra, C. A. C." box="[549,822,873,900]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="109 - 117" refId="ref10601" refString="Moure, J. S. &amp; Seabra, C. A. C. (1960) Sobre a identidade de algumas especies de Centris (Hymenoptera - Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 9, 109 - 117." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure &amp; Seabra (1960)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is poorly known and females have never been associated with the males. Therefore potential synonymies have not been possible to assess.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,152,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">
As indicated in the treatment of each species, six 
<typeStatus box="[758,806,945,971]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">type</typeStatus>
series of Lepeletier were not found during the development of this research. According to the literature (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[746,956,981,1007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref10644" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[827,876,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), the primary 
<typeStatus box="[1109,1168,981,1007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1204,1317,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[1204,1223,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1236,1317,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1330,1429,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis box="[1330,1349,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1362,1429,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[151,282,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[151,170,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[184,282,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[297,439,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scapulata">
<emphasis box="[297,316,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[330,439,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">scapulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[494,619,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testacea">
<emphasis box="[494,513,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[527,619,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">testacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were supposedly deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[965,1046,1017,1043]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">MNHP</collectionCode>
, however, they were not localized, despite the search effort. Since the Lepeletier’s material deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[940,1017,1053,1079]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/q2xn-ty4w" name="Museo Civico DI Storia Naturale DI Torino" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">MSNT</collectionCode>
was not studied, it is not possible to know if the missing 
<typeStatus box="[381,440,1089,1115]" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">types</typeStatus>
are actually in that collection, or if they are definitely lost. Fortunately, all these species, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName box="[398,538,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Hemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[398,417,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[431,538,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, can be identified from their original descriptions avoiding potential taxonomic problems related to the identity of Lepeletier species.
</paragraph>
